# Blender addon operator & module testing

Agents adding or changing operators, helpers, or submodules must add or extend **colocated** tests and wire them into the **nearest aggregator** when the addon uses that pattern. Never mock `bpy` — run real headless Blender for bpy layers.

## Testing pyramid (mandatory order)

Run and fix failures **bottom-up**. Do not add higher layers until lower layers pass.

| Layer | Runtime | What to validate |
|-------|---------|------------------|
| **1 — Pure Python** | System `python` | Helper logic, planners, parsers, math — no `bpy`. Use fakes / `SimpleNamespace` / plain arrays. |
| **2 — Headless Blender (mechanical)** | `blender.exe --background` | Loadability, `poll`, correct/incorrect cases, scene/RNA/mesh assertions, PNG/hash checks where applicable. |
| **3 — UI execution** | Blender with UI or simulation harness | Panel buttons, menus, F3 search → op runs end-to-end. **Only after layers 1–2 are green** for that feature. |

Skip layers that genuinely do not apply (document in test docstring). Pure poll-guard ops may stop at layer 2.

### Layer 1 guidance

- Extract testable logic into `static_utilities/` or category helpers so layer 1 is possible.
- Run: `python path/to/test_script.py` when the script has no top-level `import bpy`.

### Layer 2 guidance

- **Mechanical validation:** assert return sets, object/collection names, mesh counts, attribute values, file outputs — not "looks okay".
- **Fixtures:** commit small source fixtures; **gitignore** regenerated `test/data/out/` trees.
- **Bootstrap:** use addon test helpers when available — do not double-call `register()` when the addon is already enabled.

### Layer 3 guidance

- Validate that UI wired in panels/menus invokes the same helper path tested in layers 1–2.

## Layout

**Sister test per script** (see `global-testing.mdc` when installed). Minimum one test case per operator when tests exist in the repo.

```
operators/<category>/
├── MYADDON_OT_MyOperator.py
└── test/
    ├── MYADDON_OT_MyOperator_test.py
    ├── test_all.py                    # category aggregator (when used)
    └── data/
        ├── in/
        └── out/                       # local outputs only; clear before run
```

- Test module: `<OperatorClass>_test.py` or `<source_stem>_test.py`.
- Repo-root `tests/` is often launchers only — follow project rules for suite tables.

## Test aggregation (`test_all.py` pyramid)

When the addon uses aggregators, every `test/` folder should have **`test_all.py`** that invokes sibling `*_test.py` and child aggregators. Parent `test_all.py` invokes child aggregators bottom-up.

**Hygiene:** each `*_test.py` clears only outputs it owns at start. Parent aggregators clear owned out trees once at batch begin — not between child subprocesses.

## Headless execution (layer 2+)

| Requirement | Value |
|-------------|-------|
| Runtime | Real `blender.exe` — **never** mock `bpy` |
| Mode | `--background` / `-b` |
| Isolation | `--factory-startup`; enable **only** the addon under test |
| Exit codes | `--python-exit-code 1`; script ends with `raise SystemExit(0|1)` |

Direct Blender:

```text
blender.exe --background --factory-startup --python-exit-code 1 --python <path/to/test_script.py>
```

Use the addon's documented test launcher when present (e.g. `tests/blender_headless.py`, `launch_headless_test.bat`).

## Test script skeleton

Docstring should include canonical launch line. Pattern: bootstrap → layer-1 cases (if any) → loadability → correct → incorrect → `main()` collecting failures → `raise SystemExit(0|1)`.

## Assertion patterns

- Operator return: `{'FINISHED'}` / `{'CANCELLED'}` — never ignore.
- Scene: object names, mesh counts, collections, registered RNA props.
- Poll: `Class.poll(context)` with `bpy.context.temp_override(...)` when needed.
- Report per-case `[PASS]`/`[FAIL]`; one non-zero exit at end.

When adding an operator or submodule, add tests and aggregator wiring in the same change unless the user explicitly defers testing.
